{"id": 231342286, "title": "Kalu Pays Tribute to Late Senator Ayogu Eze, Praises His Unparalleled Dedication To Public Service", "text": "In a statement by Levinus Nwabughiogu, Chief Press Secretary to the Deputy Speaker, Kalu described late Senator Ayogu Eze as a respected leader and man of immense character whose dedication to public service was unparalleled. Kalu made the remarks while paying tributes to late Senator Eze at his Service of Songs in Abuja, Friday night. It will be recalled that Senator Eze who passed on late April this year was a former spokeman of the Senate of the Federal Republic of Nigeria where healso represented the people of Enugu North Senatorial District from 2007 to 2015 upon his election as a lawmaker in the National Assembly. A former Commissioner for Information in Enugu State, Senator Eze was also a journalist and prolific writer. Kalu who said that Senator Eze championed the cause of his constituents and the nation throughout his time in the Senate also extolled his commitment to deepening Nigeria\u2019s democracy, stressing that the deceased left a lasting legacy that will continue to benefit Nigerians for years to come. The deputy speaker added that Senator Eze\u2019s death has created a void in the hearts of everyone who knew him even as he commiserated with the family. He said: \u201cWith a heavy heart, we gather today to remember and pay tribute to a remarkable Nigerian, Senator Ayogu Eze. Senator Eze was a respected leader and a man of immense character. \u201cHis dedication to public service was unparalleled. Throughout hisdistinguished career, Senator Eze championed the causes of his constituents and our nation with utmost devotion. \u201cFor the eight years he spent in the Senate, he was a member of the Constitution Drafting and Amendment Committee that made some novel changes to Nigeria\u2019s 1999 constitution. \u201cHe was also the official Spokesman of the Senate, serving as Chairman of the Senate Committee on Information and Media. \u201cFurthermore, his commitment to deepening Nigeria\u2019s democracy leaves alasting legacy that will continue to benefit Nigerians for years to come. \u201cBeyond his political accomplishments, Senator Eze was a man of great warmth and kindness. He was genuinely able to connect with people from all walks of life. He will be deeply missed, not only for his sharp intellect and political acumen but also for his jovial spirit and infectious laughter. \u201cTo the Eze family, I can only imagine the depth of your grief. Please know that Senator Eze\u2019s passing leaves a void not just in the APC, Enugu State, the South East, and Nigeria, but in the hearts of all who knew him. \u201cMay his memory be a blessing, and may you find solace in the knowledge that his life and service touched countless others\u201d.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"1080\" height=\"468\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" srcset=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1.jpg 1080w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1-300x130.jpg 300w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1-1024x444.jpg 1024w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1-768x333.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" /></div>In a statement by Levinus Nwabughiogu, Chief Press Secretary to the Deputy Speaker, Kalu described late Senator Ayogu Eze as a respected leader and man of immense character whose dedication to public service was unparalleled. Kalu made the remarks while paying tributes to late Senator Eze at his Service of Songs in Abuja, Friday night. [&#8230;]", "url": "https://independent.ng/kalu-pays-tribute-to-late-senator-ayogu-eze-praises-his-unparalleled-dedication-to-public-service/", "image": "https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240608-WA0003-1.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 16:26:08", "author": "Torkwase Nyiekaa", "authors": ["Torkwase Nyiekaa"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "ng", "sentiment": 0.787}